x = df.describe().T

x['iqr'] = x['75%'] - x['25%']

x['l_outlier'] = x['25%'] - (1.5 * x['iqr'])
x['l_extreme'] = x['25%'] - (3 * x['iqr'])

x['u_outlier'] = x['25%'] + (1.5 * x['iqr'])
x['u_extreme'] = x['25%'] + (3 * x['iqr'])

#Set lower outlier/extreme boundaries to 0 if negative since none of our numerical values should be negative.
x['l_outlier'] = x['l_outlier'].apply(lambda x: x if x >= 0 else 0)
x['l_extreme'] = x['l_extreme'].apply(lambda x: x if x >= 0 else 0)

x.round(2)

Target Variables:

The count and mean of the default flag tells us that out of 5960 loans in the dataset, about 20% defaulted (mean of binary input = .1995). The mean loss amount is \$13,415 and the median is \\$11,003, however, the maximum is \$78,987 which suggests that we have some extreme outliers to deal with (upper boundary for extreme outliers is \\$41,624)

Input Variables:

Every numerical input value contains extreme upper outliers that we'll have to determine what to do with as we build the predictive model. One interesting thing to note is Derogatory marks and Delinquencies both look like they're heavily skewed to the right as the majority of the loan recipients have 0 of each with maximums of 10 and 15 respectively.

REASON:
The first thing of interest here to me is that the rate of Default is slightly less when Debt Consolidation (~19%) is the reason for a loan vs. Home Improvement (~22%). Our conventional wisdom says that DebtCon should be riskier. However, looking at the loss amount, we can see that the average a bank loses for DebtCon loan defaults is nearly double that of HomeImp.

Additionally, the Loss Amount for DebtCon is nearly equal to the average Loan Amount but for HomeImp is about half of the average Loan Amount.

JOB:
The job titles here are pretty telling in that those who are 'Self Employed' tend to Default at the 2nd highest rate of 30%, result in the most loss on average and also take out the largest loans on average.

Also of note is the higher rate of Derogatory Marks for those who are in Sales. Maybe this is due to the instability of a commission-based role. Interestingly, the Delinquencies are much lower than others. With Self Employed individuals, the inverse is true where Delinquencies are high and Derogatory Marks are in the lower half of the 6 Job classes.

for obj in objList:

    if df[obj].isna().sum() == 0:
        
        continue
        
    print(obj + " is missing values")
    name = "IMP_" + obj
    print(name + " created")
    df[name] = df[obj]
    df[name] = df[name].fillna(value=df[obj].mode()[0])
    print()

# Get the Median numerical values for each class of each categorical value before dropping incase we want to use for imputing.
med_job = df.groupby('JOB').median().T.copy()
med_reason = df.groupby('REASON').median().T.copy()

for obj in objList:
    
    if df[obj].isna().sum() == 0:
        
        continue
        
    df = df.drop(obj, axis=1)

for flt in fltList:
    
    if df[flt].isna().sum() == 0:
        continue
        
    flag = "M_" + flt
    imp = "IMP_" + flt
    
    df[flag] = df[flt].isna() + 0
    df[imp] = df[flt]
    
    df.loc[df[imp].isna(), imp] = df[flt].median()
    
    df = df.drop(flt, axis=1)
